The paper deals with Markov decision processes (MDPs) and uncertainty sets, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of scenario optimization techniques suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the experiments involve solving optimization problems, which is a common theme in robotics (cs.RO).
